{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"alias":"savvy-bacciform-seahorse","description":"## Why\nIncident 2731: a compose-file external volume added without its compose-up.sh creation counterpart broke every deploy for 41h. `docker compose config -q` cannot catch this (host-runtime state), so the class recurs silently.\n## What\nAdd a static check (make config-check / CI) asserting each `external: true` volume name in infra/compose/docker-compose.yml appears in compose-up.sh's creation list; fail the build on drift.\n## Scope\n- Grep-level script, wired into the existing config-check seam; no YAML parser dependency.\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] Check fails when an external volume is added to docker-compose.yml without compose-up.sh support (regression test on 10837ca88's diff shape).\n- [ ] Check passes on current main once bug e991-e347-3444-427c lands.\n- [ ] Runs in CI via existing make target.","id":"b005-1833-1f50-484c","parent_id":"","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"task","title":"CI drift gate: every external volume in docker-compose.yml must be provisioned by compose-up.sh"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1783658957628761001,"uuid":"273d12ce-24cd-4153-a5a3-a52bc61003cb"}